description: From Latin trāns (“across”) + līnea (“a line”). Compare Italian tralineare, tralignare.

verbs.description: tralineate (third-person singular simple present tralineates, present participle tralineating, simple past and past participle tralineated)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To deviate; to stray; to wander.
examples: If you tralineate from your father's mind, What are you else but of a bastard kind?
